Class RubyInterpreter<T extends Organism>

  • java.lang.Object
    • objenome.op.compute.ScriptingInterpreter<java.lang.Object,T,java.lang.Object>

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.function.Function<Computer.ComputerInput<java.lang.Object,T>,java.lang.Object[]>, Computer<java.lang.Object,T,java.lang.Object>

    public class RubyInterpreter<T extends Organism>
extends ScriptingInterpreter<java.lang.Object,T,java.lang.Object>
    A RubyInterpreter provides the facility to evaluate individual Ruby expressions and execute multi-line Ruby statements.

    RubyInterpreter extends from the ScriptingInterpreter, adding ruby specific enhancements, including optimized performance.

    Since:
    2.0

    • Method Detail

      • eval

        public java.lang.Object[] eval(T program,
                               java.lang.String[] argNames,
                               java.lang.Object[][] argValues)
                        throws MalformedProgramException
        Evaluates any valid Ruby expression which may optionally contain the use of any argument named in the argNames array which will be pre-declared and assigned to the associated value taken from the argValues array. The expression will be evaluated once for each set of argValues. The object array returned will contain the result of each of these evaluations in order.
        Specified by:
        eval in interface Computer<java.lang.Object,T extends Organism,java.lang.Object>
        Overrides:
        eval in class ScriptingInterpreter<java.lang.Object,T extends Organism,java.lang.Object>
        Parameters:
        expression - an individual representing a valid Ruby expression that is to be evaluated.
        argNames - an array of arguments that each of the sets of argValues should be assigned to. The array should have equal length to the argValues array.
        argValues - argument values to be assigned to the specified argument names. Each element is an array of argument values for one evaluation. As such there should be argValues.length evaluations and argValues.length elements in the returned Object array. The array should also have equal length to the argNames array.
        Returns:
        the return values from evaluating the expression. The runtime type of the returned Objects may vary from program to program. If the program does not return a value then this method will return an array of nulls.
        Throws:
        MalformedProgramException - if the given expression is not valid according to the language's syntax rules.

        Executes any valid Ruby program which may optionally contain the use of any argument named in the argNames array which will be pre-declared and assigned to the associated value taken from the argValues array. The program will be executed once for each set of argValues.

As such there should be argValues.length evaluations and argValues.length elements in the returned Object array. The array should also have equal length to the argNames array.
